{"info": {"author": "Srikalyan Swayampakula", "author_email": "", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": [], "description": "# microcosm-connexion\n\n## Description:\nA python library that exposes [microcosm] factories for [connexion]\n\n[Connexion][connexion] is a python library that reads a open-api/swagger spec and binds methods for a class to the spec.\nThis project provides the glue between [microcosm] projects and [connexion]. It provides the following components\n\n1. Connexion: An instance of connexion\n2. flask: An instance of flask created by connexion\n3. app: Same as flask instance.\n4. postgress_session_factory: Binds the Postgres SQLAlchemy session context to Flask\n5. connexion_error_handler: An instance of the ConnexionErrorHandler used for serializing errors\n6. configure_connexion_error_handler: Binds ConnexionErrorHandler to flask's generic error handler mechanism.\n\nThe reason for providing flask and app is to make sure that connexion's version of flask overrides [microcosm-flask]'s\napp.\n\nNote: A [cookiecutter] is created to make it easy for app developers to quickly start building APIs.\n\n[connexion]: https://github.com/zalando/connexion\n[microcosm]: https://github.com/globality-corp/microcosm\n[microcsom-flask]: https://github.com/globality-corp/microcosm-flask\n[microcsom-postgres]: https://github.com/globality-corp/microcosm-postgres\n[cookiecutter]: https://github.com/srikalyan/cookiecutter-connexion-microcosm-service\n\n\n\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/srikalyan/microcosm-connexion", "keywords": "", "license": "", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "microcosm-connexion", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/microcosm-connexion/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/microcosm-connexion/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/srikalyan/microcosm-connexion"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/microcosm-connexion/1.0.0/", "requires_dist": ["connexion[swagger-ui] (<3,>=2.4.0)", "inflection (<1,>=0.3.1)", "microcosm (<3,>=2)", "microcosm-flask (<3,>=2.2.0)", "microcosm-logging (<2.0.0,>=1.6.0)", "microcosm-postgres (<2.0.0,>=1.17.0) ; extra == 'postgres'"], "requires_python": "", "summary": "A python library that exposes microcosm factories for connexions", "version": "1.0.0", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>microcosm-connexion</h1>\n<h2>Description:</h2>\n<p>A python library that exposes <a href=\"https://github.com/globality-corp/microcosm\" rel=\"nofollow\">microcosm</a> factories for <a href=\"https://github.com/zalando/connexion\" rel=\"nofollow\">connexion</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/zalando/connexion\" rel=\"nofollow\">Connexion</a> is a python library that reads a open-api/swagger spec and binds methods for a class to the spec.\nThis project provides the glue between <a href=\"https://github.com/globality-corp/microcosm\" rel=\"nofollow\">microcosm</a> projects and <a href=\"https://github.com/zalando/connexion\" rel=\"nofollow\">connexion</a>. It provides the following components</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Connexion: An instance of connexion</li>\n<li>flask: An instance of flask created by connexion</li>\n<li>app: Same as flask instance.</li>\n<li>postgress_session_factory: Binds the Postgres SQLAlchemy session context to Flask</li>\n<li>connexion_error_handler: An instance of the ConnexionErrorHandler used for serializing errors</li>\n<li>configure_connexion_error_handler: Binds ConnexionErrorHandler to flask's generic error handler mechanism.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>The reason for providing flask and app is to make sure that connexion's version of flask overrides [microcosm-flask]'s\napp.</p>\n<p>Note: A <a href=\"https://github.com/srikalyan/cookiecutter-connexion-microcosm-service\" rel=\"nofollow\">cookiecutter</a> is created to make it easy for app developers to quickly start building APIs.</p>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 6216574, "releases": {"0.1.0": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "b398b9cf0161600a6b1cb4dad04563c4", "sha256": "87116b67b3bae91c62d0c8604851861006f1f0c992d442612e509b7c57bde86e"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "microcosm_connexion-0.1.0-py2.py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "b398b9cf0161600a6b1cb4dad04563c4", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py2.py3", "requires_python": null, "size": 3414, "upload_time": "2019-11-16T22:56:36", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2019-11-16T22:56:36.303886Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/4d/64/082868fec3e29d609d1b973f52fabb26622d05414bf2baafe966f101cfb8/microcosm_connexion-0.1.0-py2.py3-none-any.whl", "yanked": false}, {"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "d736edba848932db2d7270c5fc9adf14", "sha256": "31ac9d4c6fbb618f4e768e1e32e6725f2a2e202b4f668f1af0228209343f8438"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "microcosm_connexion-0.1.0.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "d736edba848932db2d7270c5fc9adf14", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": null, "size": 2702, "upload_time": "2019-11-16T22:56:38", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2019-11-16T22:56:38.986586Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/e8/f7/0ef59bffc0adcc45ba3bd4e70fcd0afda1164741ba3c0e752b0ec3d28243/microcosm_connexion-0.1.0.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "0.2.0": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "ec79bcd68238337dc6c96eccbea9488a", "sha256": "8ff76b2f05fab671b1191ab60c26c17379260b4b93ae5161fd928cc7ea6c20eb"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "microcosm_connexion-0.2.0-py2.py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "ec79bcd68238337dc6c96eccbea9488a", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py2.py3", "requires_python": null, "size": 3560, "upload_time": "2019-11-27T21:24:00", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2019-11-27T21:24:00.655409Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/pa